Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara State, on Monday, commiserated with the Emir of Gwanara, Alhaji Idris Sabi Kotokotogi, over the death of his wife, Hajia Hadizat. Hadizat died on Sunday at the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital following a brief illness. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “I commiserate with His Royal Highness, the Emir of Gwanara, on this sad development, and pray the Almighty Allah to forgive her shortcomings and comfort the larger Gwanara family, including Kwara State House of Assembly Speaker, Rt. Hon. Danladi Yakubu Salihu,” according to a statement by Rafiu Ajakaye, the governor’s Chief Press Secretary. The governor also prayed Allah to give the aged Emir long live and better health to continue to serve the people as one of Kwara’s first class emirs, the statement added.